OL,3,CTourist finds water pipe at source of
OL,4,CChina's 'tallest waterfall'
OL,6,F"The source of a waterfall is not what
OL,7,Fpeople came to see anyway, I don't
OL,8,Fthink it counts as lying to the
OL,9,Fpublic" said one Weibo user.
OL,11,FYuntai is not the first Chinese
OL,12,Fwaterfall to be given an artificial
OL,13,Fpush. In 2004, a dam was built to help
OL,14,Fthe Huangguoshu Waterfall in Guizhou
OL,15,Fprovince continue cascading down
OL,16,Fduring the dry season.
OL,18,FAt the time, the province applauded
OL,19,Fthe dam, saying it would "put an end
OL,20,Fto the history of Huangguoshu
OL,21,FWaterfall drying up."
